# plaud-cli

Unofficial command-line tool for [plaud.ai](https://web.plaud.ai/).  
Reverse-engineered from the Plaud web app — no official API exists.

> **Disclaimer** – This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by Plaud.  
> Use it only with your own account and in accordance with Plaud's Terms of Service.

---

## Features

- **Token-based auth** – uses the same long-lived JWT stored in `localStorage` on `web.plaud.ai`
- **Secure storage** – saves your token in the OS keychain (keyring) with a plain-file fallback
- **List** recordings in a rich table
- **View detail** – title, date, duration, summary, highlights, transcript
- **Export** a single recording to Markdown, JSON, or plain text
- **Sync** your entire library to a local directory
- `--json` flag on most commands for scripting / piping

---

## Installation

### From source (recommended)

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
# or just:
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

### Requirements

- Python ≥ 3.9
- `httpx`, `click`, `rich`, `keyring`, `python-dateutil`

---

## Obtaining your token

Plaud has no official API or developer portal. The token is a JWT stored in  
`localStorage` when you use the Plaud web app.

1. Open [web.plaud.ai](https://web.plaud.ai/) and log in.
2. Open DevTools (`F12` / `Cmd+Opt+I`) → **Console** tab.
3. Run:
   ```js
   localStorage.getItem("tokenstr")
   ```
4. Copy the full string (starts with `bearer eyJ…`).

The token is long-lived (~10 months) but will eventually expire.

---

## Quick start

```bash
# Store your token (prompts if not given via --token)
plaud login

# Verify it works
plaud whoami

# List all recordings
plaud list

# Full detail for one recording
plaud detail <file_id>

# Export to Markdown
plaud export <file_id> -o my-note.md

# Bulk sync entire library to ./notes/
plaud sync ./notes/
```

---

## Commands

### `plaud login`

```
plaud login [--token TEXT]
```

Prompts for your token and stores it in the OS keychain (falls back to  
`~/.config/plaud-cli/config.json`).

---

### `plaud logout`

Removes the stored token.

---

### `plaud whoami`

Validates your token by calling the API.

---

### `plaud list`

```
plaud list [--json] [--limit N] [--no-trash]
```

| Flag | Default | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `--json` | off | Print raw JSON array |
| `--limit N` | 0 (all) | Limit number of rows |
| `--no-trash` | on | Hide trashed recordings |

---

### `plaud detail <FILE_ID>`

```
plaud detail <file_id> [--json] [--hydrate/--no-hydrate]
```

Shows title, date, duration, summary, highlights and transcript.  
`--hydrate` (default on) fetches transcript/summary from signed URLs when  
the detail endpoint omits them.

---

### `plaud export <FILE_ID>`

```
plaud export <file_id> [--format markdown|json|txt] [-o OUTPUT]
```

Exports a single recording.  Output goes to stdout unless `-o` is given.

---

### `plaud sync <OUTPUT_DIR>`

```
plaud sync ./notes/ [--format markdown|json|txt] [--since 2024-01-01]
```

Bulk-exports every recording (or only those newer than `--since`) into  
`OUTPUT_DIR`.  File names follow the pattern `YYYY-MM-DD_<title>.<ext>`.

---

### `plaud config`

```
plaud config show
plaud config set-api <URL>
```

Override the API base URL (default `https://api.plaud.ai`).

---

## Environment variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `PLAUD_TOKEN` | Token override — skips keychain lookup |

---

## Project structure

```
src/plaud_cli/
├── cli.py          # Click commands
├── api.py          # HTTP client + hydration
├── normalizer.py   # Payload normalization
├── config.py       # Token / config storage
└── __init__.py
```

